<title>API Reference</title>

<h2>Reference</h2>

<h4>Core Concept - Query Parameters</h4>
<p>
    This is the API query syntax that determines what entities to retrieve and filter within a DAO. 
    The DAO gives access to source data through a generic interface. Any existing field can be queried.
</p>
<p>
    The query syntax is URL encoded. It is composed of predicates (e.g. true/false logic) and linked by operators 
    and modifiers which add conditions to the predicates. (e.g. ‘and’ = both input predicates are TRUE).
</p>
<p>
    <b>Query Syntax Glossary</b>
    <ul>
        <li>q represents the query parameter for retrieving requests (e.g. cmd=select)</li>
        <li>%3D represents ‘=’ in an encoded URL</li>
        <li>%20 represents a space in an encoded URL</li>
        <li>%3A represents a ‘:’ in an encoded URL</li>
    </ul>
</p>
<p>
    <b>Query Syntax Functions</b>
    <p>Use this query syntax to:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>
            Retrieve all entities that EQUAL a specific value.
            <blockquote><i>
                <p>Example: The name equals to the string "Ontario"</p>
                q=name%3DOntario
            </i></blockquote>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>Retrieve all entities that EQUAL a specific value with an ‘OR’ condition:</p>
            <blockquote><i>
                <p>Example: The name equals to the string "Ontario" or "Alberta"</p>
                q=name%3DOntario%20OR%20name%3DAlberta
            </i></blockquote>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>Retrieve all entities which CONTAIN a specific value:</p>
            <blockquote><i>
                <p>Example: The name contains the string "Ontario"</p>
                q=name%3AOntario
            </i></blockquote>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>Retrieve all entities which equal a specific value with an ‘AND’ condition:</p>
            <blockquote><i>
                <p>Example: The id equal to "1234" and the name equal to the string "Ontario"</p>
                q=id=1234%20AND%20name=Ontario
            </i></blockquote>
        </li>
    </ol>
</p>

